text.tspan: what color are 14 and 15? does 14 synapse on 15, and 15 on 1?
14 is a local circuit neuron, 15 may be processing stretch sensation
interoception relaying cardiovascular status, CNS ascending neuron
All monopolar neurons (neurons with only a single line leaving the soma)
in this model have dendrites but they are implicit in the notation and
have the same location as the soma.
If a neuron is colored as sensory then the longer process is the dendrite,
but in reality you should check the topology for a connection onto another
neuron. Axons are always explicit and always fully connected to the soma.
